    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a pristine 1993 Mazda RX-7 FD, maintained to exacting factory standards. The 13B-REW power plant exhibits perfect compression across all rotors, with the sequential twin-turbocharger system delivering a seamless transition at 4,500 RPM. This specimen retains its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and unmolested chassis rigidity, free from any subframe oxidation. The drivetrain features the factory 5-speed manual transmission paired with a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring optimal torque vectoring. Every vacuum line in the 'rat's nest' has been replaced with high-temp silicone, and the cooling system has been refreshed with a multi-pass aluminum radiator to mitigate heat soak. This is a collector-grade example of 90s JDM engineering, showing zero signs of synchro wear or boost leaks.",
